# PrestaShop module delivery checklist (hard gate)

Before finalising any task that creates or edits a module in `prestashop/modules/**`, all points below are REQUIRED.
If any point fails, do not deliver yet.

## 1) Frontend assets boundary

- Frontend SCSS/JS MUST live in `_dev/**` only.
- Never create module FO assets in:
  - `prestashop/modules/<module>/views/css/*` (except security `index.php`)
  - `prestashop/modules/<module>/views/js/*` (except security `index.php`)
- Module templates may render markup only; behaviour/styles come from `_dev` bundles.
- Do not call `registerStylesheet()` / `registerJavascript()` in module PHP for FO assets.

## 2) New module required files

Every new module MUST include:

- `<module>.php` (main class)
- `config.xml`
- `config_pl.xml`
- `logo.png`
- `index.php` in every directory (root + subdirectories)

Minimum expected tree:

- `prestashop/modules/<module>/index.php`
- `prestashop/modules/<module>/views/index.php`
- `prestashop/modules/<module>/views/css/index.php`
- `prestashop/modules/<module>/views/js/index.php`
- `prestashop/modules/<module>/views/templates/index.php`
- and `index.php` in each templates child folder (e.g. `admin/`, `hook/`)

## 3) Module metadata and conventions

- Author MUST be `Rafal Majdan` in both PHP and XML.
- Back-office texts: Polish by default with domain `Modules.<TechnicalName>.Admin`.
- If module renders display hook content, implement `WidgetInterface`.

## 4) Theme integration conventions

- Reusable CTA links/buttons must use `{include file='_partials/button.tpl' ...}`.
- For sliders/carousels, use `Splide.js`.
- Add SCSS section partial in `_dev/css/custom/sections/` and forward it from `_dev/css/custom/sections/_index.scss`.
- Add JS initialiser in `_dev/js/custom/Sections/` and run it from `_dev/js/custom/theme.js`.

## 5) Final verification before response

- Run `php -l` on module main class file.
- Run lints for edited files.
- Ensure no FO asset file remains in module `views/css` or `views/js` besides `index.php`.
